             One person died and 42 others were
injured yesterday when Switzerlandâ€™s Glacier Express train
derailed on the line between Zermatt and St. Moritz, the
Associated Press reported.  
 Two cars of the tourist train went off the tracks and a
third tipped over, the report said, citing Valais authorities.
Most of the injured were Japanese, AP cited the  Swissinfo  Web
site as saying. Police said 12 of the injuries were serious,
according to the report.  
